title: Fast Money trader Karen Finerman on her top investment strategies
text: Karen Finerman, Metropolitan Capital CEO, joins 'The Exchange' to discuss her investing strategies and why she says it's never too late to start investing.

title: Markets open higher as industrial stocks lead
text: CNBC's Bob Pisani looks ahead at the day's market action.

title: The economy is stronger than people think, economist says
text: First-time claims for state unemployment benefits were expected to total 216,000 for the most recent week, up from 211,000 claims reported for the previous week. American Action Forum President Douglas Holtz-Eakin joins "Squawk Box" to discuss the data and what it means for the economy.

title: Pilot-less air taxi takes off in Vienna demonstration flight
text: As carmakers push ahead with self-driving vehicles, an Austrian aerospace company and its Chinese partner showed off their pilot-less "flying taxi" for the first time in Europe on Thursday.

title: The Market Is Where It Should Be, Says Nuveen's Doll
text: Apr.04 -- Bob Doll, chief equity strategist at Nuveen, discusses the state of markets, the U.S. economy, and earnings expectations.

title: Watch one investor analyze the recent break out in the markets
text: Katie Stockton, founder and managing partner at Fairlead Strategies, joins 'Squawk Box' to discuss what she's watching in the markets.

title: Pimco Says U.S. Economy Not as Late Cycle as Many Thought
text: Apr.04 -- Joachim Fels, global economic advisor at Pimco, discusses the potential for a U.S. recession and concerns about the European Central Bank to counter a recession.

title: How this start-up is trying to disrupt the oil industry with technology
text: Xuan Yong, CEO and founder of RigUp, joins "Squawk Up" to explain his start-up, which is looking to disrupt the oil industry with tech.

title: Pimco's Fels Sees Interest Rates 'Flatlining at the New Neutral'
text: Apr.04 -- Joachim Fels, global economic advisor at Pimco, explains the factors he sees keeping interest rates flat in the future. He speaks with Bloomberg's Tom Keene on "Bloomberg Surveillance.

title: Tendayi Kapfidze talks housing
text: Tendayi Kapfidze, Lending Tree Chief Economist, dicusses falling mortgage rates, a surge in refinancing, and low housing inventory

title: MIT terminates funding and research links with China's Huawei and ZTE
text: The Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) is terminating all research and funding links with Chinese tech companies Huawei and ZTE in light of recent U.S. federal probes.
